  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The proposed communication hub, by reason of its scale, design and location would fail to minimise street clutter and  harm to the character and appearance of the local area, including the setting of the adjacent Clapham Junction Conservation Area. Furthermore, the hub would create an unnecessary obstruction of the public space, hindering the convenient and safe passage of pedestrians. The proposal therefore fails to comply with the Town and Country Planning (Control of Advertisements) (England) Regulations 2007, National Planning Policy Framework (2024), the London Plan (2021), policies LP1, LP3, LP9, LP22 and LP50 of the Local Plan (2023). "
